cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a novel semi-supervised learning technique for denoising CT images obtained in the low-dose phases of coronary CT angiography. This involves the use of a cycle-consistent adversarial denoising network. Given the focus on image processing and machine learning, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves the use of a semi-supervised learning approach, which suggests that it could be relevant to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of CT imaging and medical applications could make it relevant to the cs.MM (Multimedia) sub-category. Finally, the use of adversarial networks suggests that it could be relevant to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category.
